</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uzealpath00.showPublicProfile?language=EN>ZealPath00</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_purplespot.gif BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Wizard</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(6/29/01 2:28:41 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: minimum lvl to start the Epic?</span><hr size=1> Leaning towards 51 being the requirement myself but does it really mater? 50 is a non-hell level and you can be out of it nice n' quick with the right exp strategy. How you'd get anywhere close to gathering the items needed for the epic before 54 or so is beyond me though. Some odd yet possible circumstances I suppose.<br>
<br>
BTW it makes perfect sense that you'd be passed over at a VS raid if you were below 52 (not that there are any &quot;slapped together&quot; VS raids on my server). Lures are pretty much a requirement to hit him, I suppose enticement would have a chance but I never had to use that spell myself. <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uzealpath00.showPublicProfile?language=EN>ZealPath00</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_purplespot.gif BORDER=0> at: 6/29/01 2:32:20 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uasfacadabra.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Asfa Cadabra</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(6/29/01 8:26:29 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: minimum lvl to start the Epic?</span><hr size=1> Solomen will speak to you at levels less than 50. I have the note for Camin at level 46.<br>
<br>
