<br>
I have been fortunate enough to have many friends in my guild and outside that have invited me on higher level raids, and I fully expect to have all my pieces before 50.  However, I will wait unti I hit 51 to hand them in, as I was told 51 was the minimum.  It might be 50, but I think I would rather wait until 51, just to be absolutely certain.<br>
<br>
Good luck, all who are questing our epic.<br>
 <p>Kiranoma Soulwise</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/urombusmindspire.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Rombus Mindspire</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Sorcerer</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(6/30/01 11:50:06 pm)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://wots-signatures.hypermart.net/rombus/sidepic.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: minimum lvl to start the Epic?</span><hr size=1> You can complete any and all epics at Level 50 or higher.  They were designed for 50+.  Realistically, unless you're in a guild who has a lot of extra stuff dropping, you won't see an epic until 52+. <p><BR>
